\section{Purpose}
To study the life cycle and reproduction of various protists and fungi.

\section{Background Information}
In this lab we study the lifestyle, habitat and reproduction of several protists
and fungi. Those are two important kingdoms, with unique and interesting
charastics such as the ability to photosynthesis, and to reproduce both sexually
and asexually.

\section{Procedure}
\begin{enumerate}
    \item Put the slide onto the observation deck.
    \item Use the coarse adjustment knob to move the slide into focus
    \item Switch to high power lens and sketch the slide.
    \item Repeat with all slides.
\end{enumerate}

\section{Prelab Questions}
\begin{enumerate}
    \item Why are green plants considered to be the ancestors of land plants?

        Because green algaes were the first to develop chlorophyll-based
        photosynthesis which is found in plants today, green algaes also have
        similar cell-wall structure as do modern plants. They also both store
        food as starch and share many other common traits.

    \item What two adaptations were necessary for these photosynthetic algae to
        make the transition from aquatic (water) to terrestrial (land) habitats?

        The vascular and root system allowed land based plants to efficiently
        find, transport and store water in a relatively dry environment. The
        development of the curticle in plants as a protective layer also allows
        plants to better retain water and survive on a harsher environment.

    \item Create a table or answer in complete sentences. For each of the 4
        organisms we will be observing today, identify: the life cycle, habitat,
        reproductive method, mode of digestion, and taxonomic classification (Kingdom,
        Phylum and Class).

\begin{table}[h]
    \begin{center}
        \begin{tabular}{p{0.1\textwidth}|p{0.15\textwidth}|p{0.15\textwidth}|p{0.15\textwidth}|p{0.15\textwidth}|p{0.25\textwidth}}\\
            \textbf{Organism} & \textbf{Life-cycle} & \textbf{Habitat} &
            \textbf{Reproductive Method} & \textbf{Mode of Digestion} &
            \textbf{Taxonomic Classification}\\\hline
            \textit{Spirogyra spp.} & Alternating Haploid and Diploid cycles & Fresh water & Both asexual and sexual &
            Photosynthesis & Plante, Chlorophyta, Zygnematophyceae \\\hline
            \textit{Volvox spp.} & Alternating Haploid and Diploid cycles & Fresh Water & Both asexual and sexual &
            Photosynthesis & Plante, Chlorophyta, Chlorophyceae \\\hline
